content:
Every time I listen to spotify and eventually my phone screen goes off with the app running in the background, the music starts lagging or even stops. Then, as soon as I clink the wake-up botton, the music starts flowing again. This happens with WI-FI, with mobile data and even when listening to saved songs offline.
I have tried:
- Restarting phone;
- Clean reinstall of Spotify;
- Granting spotify all permissions, including the one to run in background, unrestricted data access and everything that was possible to grant;
- I manually chose NOT to optimize battery only for spotify;
- I disabled the adaptive battery.
 NOTHING worked. Please help me fix this!

Here's the link to Spotify community forum where other users have the exact same issue: https://community.spotify.com/t5/Android/Spotify-LAG-when-open-in-background/m-p/5041845#M168756
